<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id1171474400550">
<term>ideology</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1171474202007">the beliefs and ideals that help to shape political opinion and eventually policy</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1171472180147">
<term>intense preferences</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1171474228536">beliefs and preferences based on strong feelings regarding an issue that someone adheres to over time</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1171471913309">
<term>latent preferences</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1171474476628">beliefs and preferences people are not deeply committed to and that change over time</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1171474411916">
<term>partisanship</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1171474193795">strong support, or even blind allegiance, for a particular political party</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1171474428491">
<term>social capital</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1171474478052">connections with others and the willingness to interact and aid them</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>
